{"key":"processedPost-6362742","value":{"id":6362742,"first":6360962,"last":6364380,"when":1165973325,"utime":"12/13/06 03:28 AM","content":"For a martha or larger sized greenhouse, cut the holes about 4\" in diameter.  At least two at top and at least two down low.  I have several times that many.  The more air holes you have the better, provided you can keep up with humidity, which a coolmist or two inside will easily do.  Don't let anybody mislead you either.  Lining the floor with trays of damp perlite makes a huge difference, especially if you have a fan blowing across them.<br />RR","title":"Re: Dual grow closet design questions"}}